# Community / Public Repository Documentation

This repo is **public-facing**. Documentation follows the split model in [`agent-specifications/common/community-public-repos.md`](https://github.com/relaymonkey/agent-specifications/blob/main/common/community-public-repos.md).

## Two audiences, two places

| File | Audience | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `README.md` | End users | Pitch, quick start, short "what it does", links out |
| `docs/*.md` | Developers | Config reference, local dev, contributing, deep detail |

All documentation files are **`.md`**.

## README rules

- Keep it **clear and concise** — happy path in under two minutes of reading.
- Copy-paste quick start commands; minimal prose.
- Link to `docs/` for configuration tables, dev setup and contributor workflow.
- **Do not** grow the README with full config keys, Makefile catalogues, or CI/release internals.

## `docs/` rules

- One topic per file under `docs/` (`configure.md`, `developing.md`, …).
- kebab-case filenames.
- When you add or rename a doc, add a one-line link from the README.

## When editing

- User-facing install or first-run flow changed → update `README.md`.
- Config keys, defaults, or dev workflow changed → update the relevant `docs/*.md`.
- Never duplicate long reference material in both places — README links, `docs/` holds the detail.
